ON THE HALVERSON CONTRACT.

514
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:17,300
CAN'T THIS WAIT?

515
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:20,200
THE MARKET'S ALREA OPEN
IN TOKYO.

516
00:27:20,300 --> 00:27:23,100
UH, GO AHEAD.
I'M GONNA OPEN SOME MORE WINE.

517
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:38,300
MR. YOUNG WANTS TO MAKE SURE
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT LAST PART.

518
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:39,900
DO YOU?

519
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,600
YEAH.

520
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:53,500
I GET IT.

521
00:27:56,900 --> 00:27:59,600
SO WHEN WE THINK OF JANE,

522
00:27:59,700 --> 00:28:03,200
LET US REMEMBER HER KIND HEART
AND HER LOVING SPIRIT.

523
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:06,300
AND NOW IF THERE'S SOMEONE WHO'D
LIKE TO SHARE A SPECIAL MEMORY

524
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:08,000
OF OUR DEAR FRIEND?

525
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:09,500
(Lynn) I WOULD.

526
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:19,500
HI. I'M LYNN DEAN.

527
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:22,100
JANE AND I
WERE SORORITY SISTS.

528
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:25,600
IFHE WERE HERE, SHE'D MAKE ME
SING OUR PLEDGE SONG,

529
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:28,600
BUT I THINK THERE'S ALREADY BEEN
ENOUGH GRIEF FOR ONE DAY.

530
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:35,900
NOW I KNOW HOW BADLY
WE'VE ALL FELT FOR IAN

531
00:28:35,900 --> 00:28:39,500
DURING HIS LONG, LONELY VIGIL,

532
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:44,600
SO I'M SURE YOU'LL BE AS HAPPY
AS I WAS TO LEARN

533
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:48,100
HIS VIGIL WASN'T
QUITE SO LONELY AFTER ALL.

534
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:50,600
(under breath)
OH, DEAR GOD.

535
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:55,600
NO, HE FOUND
A WARM, CARING WOMAN

536
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:57,400
TO SHARE HIS BURDEN...

537
00:28:59,100 --> 00:29:01,700
AND SO MUCH ELSE.

538
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:08,500
SOME PEOPLE MIGHT FIND THE FACT
THAT SHE'S HE TODAY

539
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:10,400
INAPPROPRIATE,

540
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:14,600
BUT I THINK SHE'S A HERO.

541
00:29:14,700 --> 00:29:21,400
SHE DARED TORAVE THE SCORN OF
THOSE WHO MIGHT FIND HER ACTIONS

542
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:26,000
QUESTIONABLE OR EVEN UNSAVORY.

543
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:27,400
OH. (chuckles)

544
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:30,300
I WAS GONNA ASK HER TO STAND,
BUT I SEE SHE ALREADY HAS.

545
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:35,800
SUSAN MAYER, SAY HELLO.

546
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:39,700
HEY.

547
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,800
WOW. (chuckles)

548
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:52,800
GUESS SOMEONE'S IN A HURRY
TO GET ON WITH THE EVENING.

549
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:55,900
YEAH.

550
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,800
WELL, I SHOULD GO.

551
00:29:57,800 --> 00:29:59,900
WHAT?

552
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,800
