ON THAT HALVERSON DEAL.

553
00:30:02,900 --> 00:30:04,600
SORRY.

554
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:06,800
BUT CAN'T IT WAIT
TILL AFTER DESSERT?

555
00:30:06,900 --> 00:30:10,600
AND BY "DESSERT," I MEAN SEX.
YOU ARE CLEAR ON THAT, RIGHT?

556
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:13,000
PAINFULLY,
BUT MY JOB'S AT STAKE HERE.

557
00:30:13,100 --> 00:30:15,500
I REALLY DON'T HAVE
MUCH OF A CHOICE.

558
00:30:15,600 --> 00:30:17,900
OH, I THINK YOU'VE GOT
LOTS OF CHOICES.

559
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,700
HERE'S ONE OF THEM.

560
00:30:19,700 --> 00:30:22,100
MMM!

561
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:28,300
HELLO?

562
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:30,800
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU' DOING?

563
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:32,300
WHAT?

564
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:34,300
I GAVE YOU AN ORDER,
AND I EXPECT YOU TO LLOW IT.

565
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:36,600
NOW GET OUT OF THERE.
Oh, I'm trying, sir.

566
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:38,700
I'm--It's just that
I'm meeting some resistance

567
00:30:38,700 --> 00:30:40,500
to the <i>plan</i>
that we've agreed on.

568
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:43,000
OKAY, SHE'S NOT LETTING
YOU LEAVE? THAT'S FI.

569
00:30:43,100 --> 00:30:44,500
HERE'S WHAT
I WANT YOU TO SAY.

570
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:46,900
UH-HUH.

571
00:30:48,100 --> 00:30:50,000
OKAY, I'LL GIVE THAT
A SHOT, SIR.

572
00:30:50,100 --> 00:30:52,300
IS THAT YOUR OFFICE?

573
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:54,900
YEAH, THEY, UH, THEY REALLY
NEED ME OVER THERE.

574
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:58,600
OKAY. SO COME BACK WHEN
YOU'RE DONE. I'LL WAIT UP.

575
00:30:58,700 --> 00:31:01,800
I CAN'T.
NO, I REALLY CAN'T.

576
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:06,400
WHAT IS WITH YOU?!

577
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,700
AN HOUR AGO,
YOU WE REALLY INTO ME,

578
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:11,600
AND--AND NOW YOU CAN'T
GET OUT FAST ENOUGH.

579
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:14,000
OKAY. TRUTH?

580
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,800
I THOUGHT I COULD DO THIS,
BUT I CAN'T.

581
00:31:16,900 --> 00:31:19,400
I'M JUST NOT ATTRACTED
TO YOU.

582
00:31:19,500 --> 00:31:21,800
OF COURSE YOU ARE!

583
00:31:21,900 --> 00:31:24,000
NO. SEE...

584
00:31:24,100 --> 00:31:26,500
I REALLY ONLY DATE
WOMEN IN THEIR 20s.

585
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:27,700
WHAT?

586
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:29,000
SORRY.

587
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:31,000
YOU'RE TOO OLD FOR ME.

588
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:42,100
I STILL GOT A LOT OF KICK
FOR AN OLD BROAD, DON'T I?!

589
00:32:22,500 --> 00:32:23,800
AAH!

590
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,700
MOM?

591
00:32:28,100 --> 00:32:29,700
MOM?

592
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,700
MOM, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

593
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:34,300
DON'T MOVE HER. SHE MIGHT HAVE
BROKEN SOMETHING.

594
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,900
YES, WE NEED
AN AMBULANCE, PLEASE,

595
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:40,500
AT 4354 WISTERIA LANE.

596
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:44,400
MY WIFE'S HAD A BAD FALL.
PLEASE HURRY.

597
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:54,500
How is this

598
00:32:58,100 --> 00:32:59,700
??? WAS VERY LUCKY.

599
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:01,700
SHE ONLY SUFFERED
A SLIGHT CONCUSSION.

600
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:05,900
IF YOU HAVE ANY MORE QUESTIONS,
THE DOCTOR SHOULD BE BACK SOON.
THANK YOU.

601
00:33:07,700 --> 00:33:11,100
THANK GOD.
I WAS SO WORRIED.

602
00:33:11,100 --> 00:33:13,300
YEAH, I'LL BET.

603
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:16,700
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

604
00:33:16,700 --> 00:33:19,700
I HEARD YOU TWO YESTERDAY--

605
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:22,600
ALL THAT STUFF
ABOUT YOU MAYBE GOING TO JAIL.

606
00:33:22,700 --> 00:33:25,500
WELL, THAT'S NONE
OF YOUR BUSINESS.

607
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:29,700
BUT IF YOU THINK I HAD ANYTHING
TO DO WITH BREE FALLING--

608
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:31,400
I'M NOT STUPID.

609
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:34,400
I KNOW THE COPS HAVE BEEN ALL
OVER YOU ABOUT THAT DEAD WOMAN,

610
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:36,500
AND MOM SAID FOR YOU
TO FIX IT, OR SHE WOULD.

611
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:39,000
IS THIS--IS THIS "ACCIDENT"
HOW YOU FIXED IT?

612
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:41,900
ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE UPSET.
I GET IT.
NO, NO, YOU <i>DON'T</i> GET IT.

613
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:45,400
THERE'S A REASON MY MOM PUT ME
OUT ON THE STREET LAST YEAR.

614
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:48,400
YOU'VE NEVER MET THAT GUY.
YOU'VE NEVER MET BAD ANDREW.

615
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:51,900
BUT HURT MY MOM,
AND YOU WILL.

616
00:33:51,900 --> 00:33:54,200
I LOVE YOUR MOTHER.

617
00:33:54,300 --> 00:33:57,700
I'M GONNA DO EVERYTHING I CAN
TO PROTECT HER.

618
00:33:57,800 --> 00:34:00,100
YEAH, SO AM I.

619
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:07,000
HI. I'M BREE HODGE'S SON.
YOU SEE THAT GUY RIGHT THERE?

620
00:34:07,100 --> 00:34:09,100
THAT'S HER HUSBAND.

621
00:34:09,100 --> 00:34:12,200
DO NOT UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES
LET HIM BE ALONE WITHER.

622
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:13,300
WHY?

623
00:34:13,300 --> 00:34:15,500
BECAUSE IT'S HIS FAULT
THAT SHE'S IN HERE.

624
00:34:15,500 --> 00:34:17,900
HE'S A DANGEROUS GUY.
NOW I'VE WARNED YOU.

625
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:20,500
IF ANYTHING HAPPENS TO HER,
YOU'RE LIABLE.

626
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,800
NIGHT, DAD.

627
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:41,100
OH, YOU'RE HOME.

628
00:34:41,200 --> 00:34:44,000
I THOUGHT YOU'D STILL BE OUT
ON YOUR DATE.

629
00:34:44,100 --> 00:34:46,000
DATE'S OVER.
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

630
00:34:46,100 --> 00:34:49,000
OH, I-I THOUGHT SINCE I CAN'T
TAKE YOU OUT FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY,

631
00:34:49,100 --> 00:34:51,900
I'D AT LEAST
LEAVE YOU A PRESENT.

632
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:55,400
DON'T WORRY.
IT'S--IT'S NOT EXPENSIVE.

633
00:34:59,300 --> 00:35:02,200
AW, ZACH! (giggles)

634
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:05,900
SO HOW'D YOUR DATE GO?

635
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:08,500
IS HE CRAZY?
YOU'RE NOT OLD.

636
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,200
HMM...

637
00:35:10,300 --> 00:35:13,200
YOU DID NOT SEE THE LOOK ON HIS
FACE WHEN I TRIED TO KISS HIM.

638
00:35:13,300 --> 00:35:17,100
IT'S LIKE HE WAS
SNIFFING EXPIRED MILK.

639
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:20,700
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.
YOU'RE GORGEOUS,

640
00:35:20,700 --> 00:35:23,600
AND YOU'RE JUST GONNA
GET PRETTIER EVERY YEAR.

641
00:35:23,700 --> 00:35:26,100
AW, THAT'S SO SWEET...

642
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:28,300
BUT IT'S A LIE.

643
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:32,200
EVERY TICK OF THE CLOCK
TAKES AWAY SOMETHING.

644
00:35:32,300 --> 00:35:36,800
ZACH, WHAT AM I GONNA DO
WHEN I'M NOT PRETTY ANYMORE?

645
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:42,100
THAT'S NEVER GONNA HAPPEN.

646
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:45,600
I'M GONNA
TAKE A LITTLE NAP, OKAY?

647
00:35:45,700 --> 00:35:47,400
JUST FOR A MINUTE.

648
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:52,100
TAKE AS LONG AS YOU LIKE.

649
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:08,400
SUSAN, I'VE LOOKED EVERYWHERE
FOR YOU.

650
00:36:08,500 --> 00:36:11,600
I DIDN'T THINK
TO START WITH THE, UM...

651
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:13,800
EMBALMING ROOM.

652
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:16,900
YEAH. I'LL BE HAVING
NIGHT TERRORS FROM NOW ON...

653
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:20,500
(sniffles) WHICH I DESERVE.

654
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:23,800
LOOK, NO ONE IS JUDGING YOU.

655
00:36:23,900 --> 00:36:26,300
IF ANYTHING, THEY'RE JUDGING
THAT DREADFUL LYNN.

656
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:29,000
I SHOULD BE THANKING YOU
FOR DRIVING HER AWAY.

657
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:32,100
IT USUALLY TAKES A CRUCIFIX
AND SOME GARLIC.

658
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:35,000
I'M SO SORRY
I RUINED JANE'S FUNERAL.

659
00:36:35,100 --> 00:36:36,900
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

660
00:36:36,900 --> 00:36:38,900
(sobbing) YES, I DID.

661
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:42,300
IT'S JUST...

662
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:43,700
WHAT?

663
00:36:45,700 --> 00:36:50,200
I THOUGHT AFTER WE GOT THROUGH
THIS REALLY... PAINFUL DAY,

664
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:52,200
THINGS WOULD START
TO GET BETTER.

665
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:59,100
I THOUGHT I COULD BE
MORE A PART OF YOUR WORLD.

666
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:02,100
NOW ALL YOUR FRIENDS AND FAMILY
ARE JUST GONNA THINK OF ME

667
00:37:02,100 --> 00:37:04,600
AS THE CRAZY LADY
FROM JANE'S FUNERAL.

668
00:37:04,700 --> 00:37:07,800
OH, GOD. OH, IAN.

669
00:37:07,900 --> 00:37:10,300
OKAY, THIS IS NOT
SUPPOSED TO BE ABOUT ME.

670
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:14,400
YOU SHOULD BE UPSTAIRS...
SAYING GOOD-BYE.

671
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:18,600
(sighs) I'M JUST GONNA HIDE OUT
HERE WITH THE DEPARTED

672
00:37:18,700 --> 00:37:21,600
UNTIL EVERYBODY LEAVES.

673
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:23,900
NO.

674
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:25,600
NO MORE HIDING.

675
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:28,400
WE HAVE BEEN DOING IT
FAR TOO LONG

676
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:31,600
YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

677
00:37:31,700 --> 00:37:34,600
YOU HELPED ME THROUGH THE MOST
DIFFICULT PART OF MY LIFE.

678
00:37:34,700 --> 00:37:37,600
I LOVE YOU, AND I WANT TO SPEND
THE REST OF MY LIFE WITH YOU.

679
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:39,600
I WANT TO MARRY YOU.

680
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:42,100
IAN,
ARE YOU PROPOSING TO ME?

681
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:47,700
WELL...
I GUESS MAYBE I... I AM.

682
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:51,800
WHOA, WHOA! UM, BEFORE YOU
SAY ANOTHER WORD...

683
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:54,600
TAKE A LOOK AROUND.

684
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:56,600
AH. RIGHT.

685
00:37:56,700 --> 00:37:59,500
I HADN'T REALLY THOUGHT A LOT
ABOUT THIS MOMENT,

686
00:37:59,500 --> 00:38:01,600
BUT--BUT WHEN I DID, UM,

687
00:38:01,700 --> 00:38:04,000
THE TABLE WE WERE AT
DIDN'T HAVE A BLOOD GUTTER.

688
00:38:04,100 --> 00:38:07,000
THEN MAY I
REOPEN THE SUBJECT

689
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:09,900
AT A MORE OPPORTUNE
TIME AND PLACE?

690
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:14,600
YES.

691
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:21,100
I ACCEPT
YOUR PROPOSAL TO PROPOSE.

692
00:38:22,900 --> 00:38:24,000
SHALL WE?

693
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:35,800
NOW I WANT YOU TO DIG DEEP.

694
00:38:35,900 --> 00:38:38,000
IF YOU FEEL
YOUR MEMORY BLOCKED,

695
00:38:38,100 --> 00:38:42,200
JUST COUNT TO THREE,
AND THE BLOCK WILL MELT AWAY.

696
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:47,100
IT IS NATURAL AND EASY
FOR YOU TO RECALL YTHING.

697
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:50,200
NOW REMEMBER
MONIQUE POLIER.

698
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:53,400
REMEMBER THE NIGHT
YOU MET HER.

699
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:59,000
MS. POLIER?

700
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:01,900
I'VE, UH... GOT THAT PART
FOR THE SINK.

701
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,000
HELLO?

702
00:39:16,300 --> 00:39:20,100
SORRY. UH, MONIQUE'S UPSTAIRS
TAKING A NAP.

703
00:39:20,200 --> 00:39:22,300
SHE WASN'T FEELING WELL.

704
00:39:26,900 --> 00:39:29,300
MIKE?
DID YOU SEE SOMETHING?

705
00:39:32,900 --> 00:39:34,500
I'M HER BOYFRIEND.

706
00:39:34,500 --> 00:39:38,700
I, UH, AHEM, FIGURED SHE'D WANT
TO WAKE UP TO A CLEAN KITCHEN.

707
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:42,400
UH, WELL, I'LL JUST
FINISH UP WITH THE SINK

708
00:39:42,500 --> 00:39:44,400
AND BE OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

709
00:39:44,500 --> 00:39:47,800
UH, WHY DON'T YOU LET ME
TAKE CARE OF THE SINK?

710
00:39:47,900 --> 00:39:51,100
I MEAN, I'M PRTY HANDY,
AND IT'S GETTING LATE.

711
00:39:51,100 --> 00:39:53,000
OH, I DON'T MIND STAYING.

712
00:39:53,100 --> 00:39:56,600
NO, LOOK, IT'S OKAY.
I-I GOT IT UNDER CONTROL.

713
00:39:56,600 --> 00:39:58,300
HERE.

714
00:39:58,400 --> 00:40:00,900
WELL, THIS SHOULD COVER
WHAT WE OWE YOU.

715
00:40:06,300 --> 00:40:08,700
TELL MS. POLIER
I HOPE SHE FEELS BETTER.

716
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:10,500
WILL DO.

717
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:13,600
OH, HEY...

718
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:15,800
DON'T FORGET YOUR WRENCH.

719
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:24,600
MIKE?
WH--WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

720
00:40:24,700 --> 00:40:25,800
MIKE!

721
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:35,300
UH, HEY, MR. DELFINO.

722
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:37,800
I NEED TO, UH,
TALK TO YOUR STEPDAD.

723
00:40:37,900 --> 00:40:41,600
ORSON'S NOT HERE. HE WENT
TO THE HOSPITAL WITH MY MOM.

724
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:44,500
SHE'S FINE!
THANKS FOR ASKING!

